## 🌐 DNS Troubleshooting (Break & Fix)

### Scenario:

User could not log in due to DNS misconfiguration.

### Issue:

* DNS set to 8.8.8.8 instead of domain DNS

### Troubleshooting Steps:

* ipconfig /all
* nslookup alusani.local
* dcdiag /test:dns

### Resolution:

* Restored correct DNS settings
* Flushed DNS cache
* Forced Group Policy update

```bash
ipconfig /flushdns
gpupdate /force
```

